[38;5;129m│[0m Cute, right?\n    </p>\n    <h2>The Myth, The Legend</h2>\n    <p>\n         [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m As many of you know, my journey in the cyber realm is paved with the         [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m shattered dreams of those who dared to challenge my digital fortress. It\'s  [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m not just about the skills, but the sheer audacity to think outside the       [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m box—something our little intruder sorely lacks.\n    </p>\n    <h2>Script    [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m Kiddie\'s Folly</h2>\n    <p>\n        Let\'s set the scene: a quiet night,  [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m the hum of server fans filling the air, and then, a blip. A laughable        [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m attempt to exploit a well-documented LFI vulnerability. For those in the     [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m know, LFI lets you include files on a server through the web browser. It\'s  [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m like trying to sneak into a dragon\'s lair wearing a suit made of steaks.    [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m But alas, this dragon bites back.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n        Our intrepid   [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m hacker, let\'s call them "PwnZilla123," decided it was their moment to shine [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m by dropping a URL parameter straight out of a "Hacking 101" YouTube          [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m tutorial. Unfortunately for PwnZilla123, not only does my site run on a      [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m fortress of custom-coded security, it also snickers at such pedestrian       [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m moves.\n    </p>\n    <h2>Philosophy of a Hacker</h2>\n    <p>\n             [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m While I craft digital shields and wield binary swords, I also preach and     [38;5;129m│[0m
[38;5;129m│[0m practice the ethical creed. My battlefield is strewn with the fallen scripts [38;5;129m│[0m
