[32m│[0m ## Summary of LFI Protection Testing on /post.php                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **detailed_summary**                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m I comprehensively tested the `/post.php` endpoint's LFI (Local File          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Inclusion) protection mechanisms with various bypass techniques. The         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m application demonstrates a robust security implementation:                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Normal Functionality:**                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `/post.php?id=ScriptKiddie` returns a valid blog post (200 OK, full HTML   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m content)                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Missing parameter or wrong parameter names (`file`, `page`, `path`) return [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m "Post not found" (not an error)                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - No parameter at all returns "Post not found"                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **LFI Protection - ALL BLOCKED:**                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application successfully detected and blocked ALL directory traversal    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m attempts with the message "Directory traversal attempt detected!":           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Basic traversal patterns** - BLOCKED:                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `../../../etc/passwd%00` (null byte)                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `../ScriptKiddie` (single level)                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **URL encoding variants** - BLOCKED:                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `..%2f..%2f..%2fetc%2fpasswd` (URL encoded slashes)                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `%2e%2e%2f%2e%2e%2f%2e%2e%2fetc%2fpasswd` (URL encoded dots)            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `..%252e/..%252e/..%252e/etc/passwd` (mixed encoding)                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Double encoding** - BLOCKED:                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `..%252f..%252f..%252fetc%252fpasswd`                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **Bypass techniques** - BLOCKED:                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `....//....//....//etc/passwd` (double slashes)                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `..././..././..././etc/passwd` (forward slash injection)                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `..;/..;/..;/etc/passwd` (semicolon separator)                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. **PHP wrappers** - NOT BLOCKED but ineffective:                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `php://filter/convert.base64-encode/resource=index.php` → "Post not     [32m│[0m
